  "text": "The use of viral antigens has some limitations mainly related to biosecurity and standardization concerns. Although recombinant antigens are a good alternative to avoid the use of live virus, [CITATION_1] the sensitivity of the test can differ. Recently, our laboratory (INGENASA, Madrid, Spain) has expressed different fragments of the VP72 protein with very good yields of expression in a baculovirus system. However, the reactivity of this recombinant protein in several immunoassays was in all cases lower than that of the viral antigen (data not published).",
